docs.abstract: A feminist and a self-proclaimed revolutionary, she was in the forefront of the fledgling movement for economic and political equality in the 1940s.
docs.snippet: A feminist and a self-proclaimed revolutionary, she was in the forefront of the fledgling movement for economic and political equality in the 1940s.
docs.lead_paragraph: Esther Cooper Jackson, whose voice for racial equality in the 1940s would elevate her into the vanguard of the civil rights revolution of the mid-20th century, died in Boston on Aug. 23, two days after her 105th birthday.

headline.main: Esther Cooper Jackson, Civil Rights Pioneer, Dies at 105
headline.print_headline: Esther Cooper Jackson, 105, Dies; Pioneer of Civil Rights Movement

docs.abstract: A new series of essays captures American theater as it attempts to reject some of its foundational inequities.
docs.snippet: A new series of essays captures American theater as it attempts to reject some of its foundational inequities.
docs.lead_paragraph: Forty years ago, Jesse Green, then a recent college graduate with a degree in English and theater, was a general assistant at the Williamstown Theater Festival. He made waffles, cleaned toilets and performed other work, all of it unpaid and “some of it unsafe and some of it degrading,” he wrote later.

docs.abstract: No social app remains free of arguments over politics and social issues once it becomes popular.
docs.snippet: No social app remains free of arguments over politics and social issues once it becomes popular.
docs.lead_paragraph: There is a predictable trajectory for social media apps. Many of them start out as helpful or even pure fun. But when they get popular enough, just about every app becomes a place for consequential discussions about politics and social issues, too. And with that comes both meaningful conversations and a litany of nastiness.

headline.main: Wasn’t TikTok Supposed to Be Fun?
headline.print_headline: Wasn’t TikTok Supposed to Just Be Fun?

docs.abstract: Despite the grim headlines, 2022 is less violent so far than last year.
docs.snippet: Despite the grim headlines, 2022 is less violent so far than last year.
docs.lead_paragraph: Crime, murder and mass shootings have dominated headlines this year. Just over the weekend, a shooting in Cincinnati wounded nine people, and another in Detroit killed one and wounded four.

docs.abstract: Kelly Goodlett, the former detective, pleaded guilty to one count of conspiracy. She is the first officer to be convicted in the fatal police operation.
docs.snippet: Kelly Goodlett, the former detective, pleaded guilty to one count of conspiracy. She is the first officer to be convicted in the fatal police operation.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOUISVILLE, Ky. — A former police detective admitted on Tuesday that she had helped mislead a judge into wrongly authorizing a raid of Breonna Taylor’s apartment in Louisville, Ky., setting in motion the nighttime operation in which the police fatally shot Ms. Taylor.

headline.main: Ex-Detective Admits Misleading Judge Who Approved Breonna Taylor Raid
headline.print_headline: Ex-Detective Admits  Conspiracy to Mislead Judge on Taylor Raid

docs.abstract: The influential committee called on the Biden administration to safeguard access for minorities and to address a host of issues on race relations.
docs.snippet: The influential committee called on the Biden administration to safeguard access for minorities and to address a host of issues on race relations.
docs.lead_paragraph: GENEVA — An influential United Nations panel that examined the state of race relations in the United States called on the Biden administration on Tuesday to address a host of concerns, including imperiled abortion access for minorities, curbs on voting rights and the country’s “increasingly militarized approach” to immigration.

headline.main: U.N. Race Panel Sounds the Alarm on Abortion Access in the U.S.
headline.print_headline: U.S. Abortion Access Alarms U.N. Panel

docs.lead_paragraph: As he contemplates a third straight run for the presidency, Donald Trump has a multimillion-dollar political machine and a network of tax-exempt advocacy groups at his disposal. He also has a plan. The plan is to wrest control of the federal government from what he sees as a policy apparatus dominated by “radical left-wing Democrats.”

headline.main: Trump Has Big Plans for 2025, and He Doesn’t Care Whether You Think He’ll Win

docs.abstract: The well-financed women’s club came to represent an Instagram-friendly, for-profit feminism. Then its lofty flight crashed.
docs.snippet: The well-financed women’s club came to represent an Instagram-friendly, for-profit feminism. Then its lofty flight crashed.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Wing, the women’s-only social club and co-working space that opened in New York in 2016, has been shut down by its parent company. For many professional women, the Wing, which grew to have locations in San Francisco, Chicago and Los Angeles, came to represent an empowerment movement following the election of Donald Trump.

headline.print_headline: The Wing Closes After a Turbulent Few Years

docs.lead_paragraph: WILMINGTON, Ohio — After an hourslong standoff that closed an interstate and disrupted rural life, law enforcement officers shot and killed a man who they said tried to break into the F.B.I.’s Cincinnati office on Thursday.

docs.abstract: Work by Do Ho Suh, being shown in Seoul and New York in September, highlights the global nature of the art world — and of his own personal journey.
docs.snippet: Work by Do Ho Suh, being shown in Seoul and New York in September, highlights the global nature of the art world — and of his own personal journey.
docs.lead_paragraph: It seems fitting that in early September, the artist Do Ho Suh has work on view in Seoul, the city where he was born and raised — at the fair Frieze Seoul from Saturday through Monday, and in a show at the Buk-Seoul Museum of Art, on view until March — as well as in a former hometown, New York City, at his longtime gallery, Lehmann Maupin.

headline.main: For This Korean Artist, Memories Are a Medium
